Description: Handle of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp; Helios head symbol?
Curator's comments: Only known from Petrie's drawing in his Journal, 1884-5, p.102, 31. Name, Archelas. Perhaps from same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, CEALEX L211.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0578)
